tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results show a mildly decreased hematocrit, slightly elevated platelet count, and markedly increased platelet distribution width, while other parameters are within normal limits. These findings may suggest mild hemodilution or early reactive thrombocytosis, but there is no evidence of anemia or leukocytosis. Correlation with clinical context and follow-up may be considered if symptoms or risk factors are present.
